Web UI: scalable ref picker, read-first records, 3-column forms

Reworked the generic UI from live-demo feedback:

- Ref fields are now an async search picker (queries the target entity by typed
  term, limit 20) instead of a combobox that loaded the whole table — it scales
  to 150k users / 1M config items. In read mode a ref shows the target's label,
  not its uuid.
- Records open in READ mode; editing is opt-in via a button, with Save/Cancel,
  and workflow actions are hidden while editing. No more falling straight into a
  form on click.
- Forms are a 3-column grid; each control spans 1/2/3 columns by type (long
  text/json/attachments full width, pickers half, short scalars a third).
- Workflow action buttons are humanized (close_incident → "Close incident")
  and primary-styled.

Pack: Supervisor can read SLAPolicy (so the SLA picker/label resolves).
